Santa Ono is a Canadian-American biologist and scholar who is currently serving as the President and Vice-Chancellor of the University of British Columbia (UBC) in Vancouver, Canada. He assumed this position in 2016, after serving as the President of the University of Cincinnati in Ohio, USA.

Ono is a renowned biologist who has conducted research in immunology and virology. He has also been recognized for his work in science communication and has given numerous public lectures and talks on science-related topics. In addition to his scientific work, Ono is also an accomplished musician and has been known to give impromptu performances on the cello.